Maps+ App Privacy Policy
IZE S.R.L. (“IZE”, “we” and “us”) respects the privacy of its users (“you”). This Privacy Policy covers how we collect, use, disclose and store your information; and what rights you have to this information in our Maps+ application (“app”). Please take a moment to familiarize yourself with our privacy practices and let us know if you have any questions.
What personal information we collect
• Location data
• Reminders data
• Bookmarks data
How we use your personal information
• Location data: Your location may be shown on the map.
• Reminders data: Incomplete location-based reminders may be shown on the map. You may edit location-based reminders. You may add new data to Reminders.
• Bookmarks data: Your location-based bookmarks may be shown on the map. You may edit and add new data.
Disclosure to third parties
• Location data: No third parties. We do not collect it to a central location.
• Reminders data: Apple. Your data is synced with Apple's Reminders app.
• Bookmarks data: No third parties. We do not collect it to a central location.
Children
We don't knowingly collect, use or disclose personal information from children under 13, or equivalent minimum age in the relevant jurisdiction.
Your rights
• Modify and delete your reminders and bookmarks data.
• Export your bookmarks data to a GPX file.
• Revoke permissions of the app to access your location and reminders data.
IZE may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we change the policy in a material way, a notice will be posted in the app with the updated Privacy Policy.
Contact: zsombor@ize.company
